<TITLE> Teacher fired for sexual harassment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  The Savar College of Finance and Management (CFM) dismissed a teacher on charges of sexual harassment on Monday. The suspended Ziaur Rahman was an English teacher. The decision came after a meeting, headed by CFM chairman Kamrul Ahsan, along with other teachers on Monday morning. Kamrul told bdnews24.com that Ziaur Rahman was dismissed on charges of sexually harassing two female teachers of the management department. The police were informed when the teacher tried to create a scene on campus. The two female teachers, however, said that Rahman used to harass them through conversation with obviously sexual connotation. They had informed the college authorities of the matter verbally. Ziaur Rahman, however, denied the complaint against him. "I am a victim of conspiracy. The college authority dismissed me on a false accusation," he said. bdnews2
